V

Vesuvius - Class in main
A subclass of monster this can be thought as a particular type of monster, has its own unique instance variables which are different from the other Monster subclasses
Vesuvius() - Constructor for class main.Vesuvius
An overloaded constructor called when there is no String in the parameter when this object is made, specifically its used when the user doesn't want to name this monster
Vesuvius(String) - Constructor for class main.Vesuvius
A constructor sets this monsters name to be the parameter name it will then set the instance variables of its superclass Monster, takes a String variable name as its parameter
View - Variable in class main.BattleWindow
A JButton which when pressed will display a description of the current monster the user is fighting to the user
view_self - Variable in class main.MainWindow
A JButton which when pressed will display to the user, a description of themselves
viewItems - Variable in class main.MenuWindow
A JButton which when pressed will either, display the users items to the user, enter, use the selected item in comboBox_1 on the selected monster in comboBox_2, or act as a "Back" button
viewItems - Variable in class main.ShopMenu
A JButton which when pressed will either display the items the user can buy, buy the item the user has selected from the dropdown menu (assuming the user has enough gold), or it may act has a "Back" button
viewMonsters - Variable in class main.MenuWindow
A JButton which when pressed will either, display the users monster to the user, enter "Monster order change mode", get the indexes from firtIndex and secondIndex and swap the positions of the monsters at those indexes, or act as a "Back" button
viewMonsters - Variable in class main.ShopMenu
A JButton which when pressed will either display the monsters the user can buy, buy the monster the user has selected from the dropdown menu (assuming the user has enough gold), or it may act has a "Back" button
